1
00:00:07,508 --> 00:00:10,444
⟨The one who saved the embezzled Risa from Kuwabara was →

2
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:12,446
It was my husband Takaku⟩

3
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:15,950
⟨Risa tells Ryo that she has no more money to give⟩

4
00:00:16,017 --> 00:00:19,453
(Lisa) Did your wife leave a will?

5
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,957
(Ryo) It's true that I looked for it, but it wasn't there.

6
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:28,029
⟨Finally, the true nature of the magical man Ryo is revealed⟩

7
00:00:30,531 --> 00:00:32,967
(Takaku) [It's said that he hid his deceased wife's will →

8
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,969
It didn't make any sense]

9
00:00:35,036 --> 00:00:38,472
[Wouldn't it have been better if he had followed the will?]

10
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:49,483
♪～

11
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:53,988
(Ryo) Even if you follow this, the money will end up...

12
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:57,491
(Nagiko) Because it's a love letter.

13
00:00:57,558 --> 00:01:00,494
You've written well, haven't you?

14
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:03,431
(Nagiko) Show it to everyone.

15
00:01:03,497 --> 00:01:08,502
(Ryo) Nagi-chan, please forgive me and I will apologize.

16
00:01:10,004 --> 00:01:12,506
>> Will you give me your back again?

17
00:01:14,508 --> 00:01:17,011
(Ryo) Hit me until you feel relieved.

18
00:01:18,512 --> 00:01:23,017
Then set me free.

19
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:29,023
(Lisa) Are you crazy?

20
00:01:32,026 --> 00:01:34,462
(Lisa) That's a goldfish.

21
00:01:34,528 --> 00:01:37,031
It's not Nagi-chan.

22
00:01:42,536 --> 00:01:44,538
(Lisa) A will?

23
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:49,043
It was there after all.

24
00:01:50,544 --> 00:01:52,480
Why can't you show it?

25
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:54,982
Is there something written? Besides heritage.

26
00:01:55,049 --> 00:01:58,986
(Ryo) It's just a will that wasn't written. (Risa) Then why do you still have it?

27
00:01:59,053 --> 00:02:00,988
It would have been better to dispose of it quickly.

28
00:02:01,055 --> 00:02:04,492
(Ryo) That's why I'm about to burn it now... (Risa) Were there words of love written on it?

29
00:02:06,494 --> 00:02:08,429
on second thoughts.

30
00:02:08,496 --> 00:02:10,931
That's why I cherished it.

31
00:02:10,998 --> 00:02:14,001
(Ryo) No! Let's burn this thing already.

32
00:02:16,003 --> 00:02:17,938
(Sound of hitting the shelf)

33
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:22,510
(Lisa) Why, why is it that person?

34
00:02:24,011 --> 00:02:28,516
I've been hurt like this for so long!

35
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:37,458
(Lisa) I thought you chose me.

36
00:02:37,525 --> 00:02:41,962
He says he seriously wants to leave his wife.

37
00:02:42,029 --> 00:02:47,468
That's why I believed you!

38
00:02:47,535 --> 00:02:52,973
I lost everything for you!

39
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:56,477
(Ryo) I understand... I understand, so stop it already.

40
00:02:56,544 --> 00:03:01,482
(Lisa) Got it? What do you understand? You don't understand anything!

41
00:03:01,549 --> 00:03:03,484
(sound of tapping)

42
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:07,421
Look.

43
00:03:07,488 --> 00:03:11,492
Isn't it beautiful? My bruise.

44
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:20,501
(Lisa) Say it again, ``You're beautiful.''

45
00:03:22,002 --> 00:03:24,438
Are you mine?

46
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:27,942
Say it's mine.

47
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:31,445
Hey, tell me!

48
00:03:31,512 --> 00:03:34,515
It's mine!

49
00:03:36,517 --> 00:03:39,453
(Ryo) I...

50
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,022
It's Lisa's.

51
00:03:44,024 --> 00:03:46,460
(Lisa) Hahahaha A-ha!

52
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:48,963
Liar! Liar!

53
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:50,965
Liar! (Sound of stomping)

54
00:03:51,031 --> 00:03:53,968
Liar! Liar! (Sound of stomping)

55
00:03:54,034 --> 00:03:57,471
(Kanako) Hey, what happened? Stay strong!

56
00:03:57,538 --> 00:04:00,474
(Lisa) Let go! >> Hey, take a look in the mirror over there.

57
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:03,043
You're really ugly right now.

58
00:04:10,484 --> 00:04:13,988
I'm already freaking out, so please stop. This sudden change in character.

59
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:18,492
Are you okay? Ryo-kun.

60
00:04:19,994 --> 00:04:21,929
(Ryo) Kill me.

61
00:04:21,996 --> 00:04:25,933
I want to die like this and go to Nagi-chan.

62
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,435
(Kanako) Hey, what are you talking about?

63
00:04:28,502 --> 00:04:32,506
(Ryo) I couldn't get anything.

64
00:04:34,008 --> 00:04:38,012
>>I also want to go to my baby.

65
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:45,452
I'm sorry Ryo-kun.

66
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:50,024
They have children without permission and involve themselves without permission.

67
00:04:52,026 --> 00:04:55,963
I was really selfish.

68
00:04:56,030 --> 00:05:00,467
Having a child without permission →

69
00:05:00,534 --> 00:05:03,037
This is also violence against women.

70
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:07,975
(Lisa) What does this mean?

71
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:17,418
(Lisa) What? This is called ``drug replacement.''

72
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,486
(Kanako) What is it? That letter.

73
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:25,926
(Lisa) Will Wife's will.

74
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:29,430
“My husband Ryo Jouchi →

75
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:31,932
Infidelity with Risa Yajima →

76
00:05:31,999 --> 00:05:36,937
Unless drug substitution is allowed→

77
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:40,441
The inheritance shall be as follows.

78
00:05:40,507 --> 00:05:45,446
Ryo Jouchi takes my psychotropic drugs→

79
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:49,950
Replace it with the allergy medicine the person takes on a daily basis →

80
00:05:50,017 --> 00:05:54,521
It has led to a significant deterioration in my health."

81
00:05:56,023 --> 00:05:58,459
(Cool) Nagi-chan→

82
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:01,962
He'll do anything to push me.

83
00:06:02,029 --> 00:06:04,898
>>The shapes are very similar, aren't they?

84
00:06:04,965 --> 00:06:06,900
(Ryo) Shut up.

85
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,403
(Lisa) Huh?

86
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:11,405
>> By the way, Ryo-kun→

87
00:06:11,472 --> 00:06:14,908
You came to the hospital to get allergy medicine.

88
00:06:14,975 --> 00:06:16,977
(Lisa) Allergy to grapes.

89
00:06:18,479 --> 00:06:22,983
(Kanako) No, but Ryo-kun, you wouldn't do something like that, would you?

90
00:06:24,985 --> 00:06:28,422
Don't answer, Ryo.

91
00:06:28,489 --> 00:06:33,927
(Lisa) Do you still have it? This is the medicine that my wife gave me that night.

92
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:35,996
(Kanako) I have it though.

93
00:06:37,998 --> 00:06:40,934
(Lisa) If you look into it, you'll find out, right?

94
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:43,437
Is it an allergy medicine?

95
00:06:43,504 --> 00:06:45,939
>> Hey, I don't know.→

96
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:48,442
Does that mean I will die if I change my medicine?

97
00:06:48,509 --> 00:06:50,444
(Ryo) I won't die. (Risa) But I died.

98
00:06:50,511 --> 00:06:54,448
(Ryo) He committed suicide. (Risa) Didn't you set him up to do that?

99
00:06:54,515 --> 00:06:59,453
It is written here that ``If you approve, you will be allowed to inherit.''

100
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:03,390
(Ryo) It's too late now.

101
00:07:03,457 --> 00:07:07,461
(Lisa) What happened that night?

102
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:12,399
What did you do to that person?

103
00:07:12,466 --> 00:07:14,968
>>I'll do anything.

104
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:19,907
(Nagiko) If it's to push me into a corner.

105
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:22,976
[coughing]

106
00:07:25,479 --> 00:07:31,919
[Haa haa…]

107
00:07:31,985 --> 00:07:35,422
〔where? Where did you hide it? ]

108
00:07:35,489 --> 00:07:39,426
[Haa haa…]

109
00:07:39,493 --> 00:07:41,428
(Ryo) [Painful? ]

110
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:44,431
>> [Ryou please...]

111
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:47,935
[Haa haa…]

112
00:07:48,001 --> 00:07:50,437
(Ryo) [Get comfortable now, Nagi-chan]

113
00:07:50,504 --> 00:07:54,942
>> [Haa ha…]

114
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:57,010
(Ryo) [disappeared]

115
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:03,884
(Lisa) Hey, what did you do?

116
00:08:03,951 --> 00:08:06,887
Ryo-kun, please answer.

117
00:08:06,954 --> 00:08:08,889
(Ryo) I haven't done anything.

118
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:11,391
Nagi-chan just left the house.

119
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:13,393
>>And jumped off.

120
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:16,396
(Ryo) It's not my fault!

121
00:08:16,463 --> 00:08:19,900
Before I knew it, it suddenly came out...

122
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:21,902
>>We still share the pain.

123
00:08:21,969 --> 00:08:24,905
(Ryo) It's because Risa showed up!

124
00:08:24,972 --> 00:08:26,907
(Lisa) Yeah.

125
00:08:26,974 --> 00:08:29,910
(Ryo) If only Risa-san didn't show up...

126
00:08:29,977 --> 00:08:34,414
(Lisa) [It must have been painful, but you endured it.]

127
00:08:34,481 --> 00:08:37,918
(Ryo's voice) I was able to avoid noticing my own pain.

128
00:08:37,985 --> 00:08:41,922
I never thought I wanted to be free.

129
00:08:41,989 --> 00:08:44,424
It's Risa's fault that Nagi-chan died.

130
00:08:44,491 --> 00:08:47,427
>> Hey, Ryo-kun. (Ryo) I haven't done anything.

131
00:08:47,494 --> 00:08:50,931
This will is a lie.I cannot be bound by something like this.

132
00:08:50,998 --> 00:08:54,001
I... I didn't do anything!

133
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:01,008
(Lisa) I understand.

134
00:09:03,010 --> 00:09:05,445
I'm not doing anything.

135
00:09:08,949 --> 00:09:10,951
(Lisa) But Ryo-kun.

136
00:09:12,953 --> 00:09:18,392
So can you really be free?

137
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:46,420
♪～

138
00:09:46,486 --> 00:09:50,424
(Nagiko's voice) ``However, someday in the future→

139
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:53,427
If Ryo changes his mind →

140
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:58,432
The right of inheritance arises again.

141
00:09:58,498 --> 00:10:01,435
At least cool →

142
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:06,506
One moment, he loved me."

143
00:10:09,509 --> 00:10:15,449
(Nagiko's voice) ``That's how I was able to live.''

144
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:18,952
Why do I →

145
00:10:19,019 --> 00:10:23,457
I guess I couldn't love Ryo properly?

146
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:26,460
Why is it cool →

147
00:10:26,526 --> 00:10:30,464
I guess I couldn't be loved properly?

148
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:32,532
I’m sorry, Ryo.”

149
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:42,542
(Lisa) I'm home.

150
00:10:44,044 --> 00:10:45,545
(Sound of turning on the light)

151
00:10:47,047 --> 00:10:49,549
(Lisa) I'm not in a position to say that.

152
00:11:02,562 --> 00:11:05,499
(Oshima's voice) Is only one senior going to move?

153
00:11:05,565 --> 00:11:09,569
(Lisa) Yeah, I'm looking for a good place.

154
00:11:11,071 --> 00:11:15,509
(Oshima) You won't get any severance pay if you are fired for disciplinary action, right?

155
00:11:15,575 --> 00:11:19,513
(Lisa) Unemployment insurance won't come out for a while.

156
00:11:19,579 --> 00:11:22,082
It may be difficult to find work again.

157
00:11:24,084 --> 00:11:26,520
>>Do you hold a grudge?

158
00:11:26,586 --> 00:11:30,090
I reported everything to the company.

159
00:11:32,592 --> 00:11:34,528
(Lisa) Thank you.

160
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:39,032
For dragging me back to this world.

161
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:44,471
I couldn't go back on my own.

162
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:46,540
Thank you.

163
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:55,549
>> I'll eat it.

164
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:08,995
I hated my senior.

165
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:11,498
(Lisa) Huh?

166
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:16,002
>> Well, I might be a little jealous right now.

167
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:18,572
My senior went crazy in love.

168
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:24,511
I wonder what will happen so indiscriminately →

169
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:27,581
I wonder if there is a future in my life.

170
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:34,521
(Lisa) But there's nothing left.

171
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:43,964
(Lisa) All that's left is to put people's money into the ATM →

172
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:47,534
The feeling of being sucked in.

173
00:12:51,037 --> 00:12:54,541
>> Is that really the only thing left?

174
00:12:57,043 --> 00:13:01,481
(Lisa) 《There's one more feeling that won't go away》

175
00:13:01,548 --> 00:13:04,985
>> I was told not to say that →

176
00:13:05,051 --> 00:13:09,990
Mr. Takahisa came to my company after that.

177
00:13:10,056 --> 00:13:13,560
``My wife caused you trouble,'' he said, bowing his head.

178
00:13:16,062 --> 00:13:20,000
What are you going to do now? senior.

179
00:13:20,066 --> 00:13:23,003
Will you go back to your old self?

180
00:13:23,069 --> 00:13:27,007
Or myself as a woman I don't know →

181
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:29,075
Are you going to survive?

182
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:36,516
(Lisa) 《I committed a crime》

183
00:13:39,519 --> 00:13:43,957
(Lisa) 《I'm always dissatisfied with my life in some way →

184
00:13:44,024 --> 00:13:46,526
Because I wanted to be different.

185
00:13:48,528 --> 00:13:50,463
(Sound of placing a bag)

186
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:55,468
(Lisa) 《Devouring the food that comes in front of you with desire →

187
00:13:55,535 --> 00:13:57,971
I lost everything》

188
00:13:58,038 --> 00:14:00,040
(sound of door closing)

189
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:03,543
(Takaku) Ah...｡

190
00:14:08,548 --> 00:14:10,483
(Takaku) It's been a while.

191
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:12,986
(Lisa) Yes.

192
00:14:13,053 --> 00:14:18,992
(Takaku) Sorry, I completely forgot to press the stamp on the divorce notification.

193
00:14:19,059 --> 00:14:23,997
If you push it, I'll go home. I'm busy with work.

194
00:14:24,064 --> 00:14:27,567
Ah... I'll take care of the delivery.

195
00:14:29,069 --> 00:14:30,570
(Lisa) Yes.

196
00:14:33,573 --> 00:14:37,944
(Takaku) The registered seal... Where is the registered seal...｡

197
00:14:38,011 --> 00:14:41,514
There was, there was, vermilion, vermilion, vermilion.

198
00:14:44,017 --> 00:14:47,454
(Lisa) Thank you for the money.

199
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,456
(Takaku) Huh?

200
00:14:49,522 --> 00:14:53,460
(Risa) I heard from Oshima-chan that she was trying to make a change.

201
00:14:53,526 --> 00:14:58,965
(Takaku) Ah, I'm just a little curious.

202
00:14:59,032 --> 00:15:01,034
(Lisa) Yes.

203
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,042
(Takaku) Here.

204
00:15:12,545 --> 00:15:14,547
(Takaku) You know...

205
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:21,054
(Takaku) All the rice balls were the ones I liked.

206
00:15:23,056 --> 00:15:26,493
(Lisa) Oh, a present?

207
00:15:26,559 --> 00:15:29,062
Sorry for leaving it there.

208
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:39,439
(Takaku) When I think that Risa slept with another man →

209
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:43,510
I'm still in pain and my heart feels like it's going to burst.

210
00:15:45,512 --> 00:15:47,447
I was the one who had the affair first →

211
00:15:47,514 --> 00:15:49,449
I know that's what caused it.

212
00:15:49,516 --> 00:15:54,454
But... But that's what I think.

213
00:15:54,521 --> 00:16:00,460
(Lisa) I still feel bad about it too.

214
00:16:00,527 --> 00:16:05,465
I remember the day I realized that Takahisa was having an affair.

215
00:16:05,532 --> 00:16:11,538
But I'm more ashamed of what I did.

216
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:16,976
Takaku is in a place I don't know →

217
00:16:17,043 --> 00:16:20,046
I think I was embarrassed a lot.

218
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:24,050
sorry.

219
00:16:27,053 --> 00:16:29,556
(Lisa) I'm really sorry.

220
00:16:32,058 --> 00:16:34,060
(Takaku) I'm sorry too.

221
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:40,433
I thought I was pretty smart →

222
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,936
When I realized that I was thinking about everything with ease →

223
00:16:43,003 --> 00:16:48,441
I mistakenly thought that it meant efficiency and wisdom.

224
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:52,946
It's true that it's about Risa and the child...

225
00:16:53,013 --> 00:16:55,014
I'm really sorry.

226
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:07,961
(Takaku) Isn't there a choice not to break up? Us.

227
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,963
(Lisa) Huh?

228
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:13,466
(Takaku) Maybe things like that between us like now →

229
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:15,468
If only I could say what I'm holding back →

230
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:17,537
I wonder if this didn't happen.

231
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:25,545
(Takaku) So, is it a bad idea to try that?

232
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,984
(Lisa) It's impossible.

233
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,986
(Takaku) No, it's not impossible.

234
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,988
(Lisa) Now is now.

235
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:37,991
There's no guarantee that you'll be able to say the same thing again.

236
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,993
(Takaku) I will try my best.

237
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,562
(Lisa) I...

238
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:47,000
I don't know if I can do it.

239
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,502
(Takaku) I will never have an affair again.

240
00:17:49,569 --> 00:17:53,006
(Lisa) That's also me...｡

241
00:17:53,073 --> 00:17:55,074
I don't know.

242
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:02,515
(Lisa) Even though I know it's hell from there→

243
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:06,085
You might want to go again on your own.

244
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:14,594
(Takaku) Well...

245
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:24,103
(Takaku) Well then, rock, paper, scissors.

246
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:27,607
(Lisa) Huh?

247
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:34,047
(Takahisa) If Risa wins in rock-paper-scissors, it's a divorce.

248
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,983
If I win, I'll continue.

249
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:40,487
That's the worst choice of words →

250
00:18:40,553 --> 00:18:42,989
I have been →

251
00:18:43,056 --> 00:18:46,059
